author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Class AA softball: Chambers leads Union County into second round
text:
By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles Class softball: Branch nets historic first round win Class AAAA softball: Buford routs Woodward in first round; gets rematch with TCC in second round Class AAAA softball: North Hall solid in first round sweep of Troup County Softball: Buford leads area teams into state playoffs 
BLAIRSVILLE — Union County moved into the second round of the Class AA girls state softball tournament Wednesday. 
The Lady Panthers, the second seed from Region 8-AA, swept Bowden 1-0 and 6-4 behind a pair of wins from Laken Chambers in the circle. Chambers struck out combined in the two games. 
Chambers also provided a spark at the plate going 4-for-7 with three RBI for Union County. Karley Nix had five hits and one RBI, Kendra Tanner had three hits, Jillian Lawn added a pair of hits, and Lydia Arrowood had a hit and two RBI for the Lady Panthers. 
Union County (23-7) next will travel to Region 4-AA champ Lamar County in the second round.Lamar County whipped Early County 9-1 and 12-2 to advance. Associated Tags : High school softball, Union County softball © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
